       <div class="vt-postcontent">
       that's exactly why everywhere on the wiki/forum the suggested way to get root access is &quot;sudo -E -s&quot; the -E stands for preserve environment variables. Also your method of using &quot;-i&quot; is correct, -i, as you can read on the sudo manual, will emulate a full user login, thus reading .profile, .basrc, and all the files where the environment is set.<br />So you can safely use it or you can use sudo -E -s, it's your call
       </div> 
       
       <div id="sig5447" class="signature">--pippone</div>

    
    
